==English==
===Adverb===
# The other way around; with the order reversed.
The phrase "vice versa" is a Latin [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ablative_absolute ablative absolute] involving the feminine third declension [[noun]] "vicis" (arrangement, order, position, etc.) and the feminine [[ablative]] singular of the perfect passive [[participle]] "versus," from the verb "verto" (turn, reverse, etc.). The phrase is literally translated, "the position having been reversed."